  "instructions": [
    "Thread beef strips onto skewers. In a large bowl whisk together soy sauce, lime juice, garlic, cumin, coriander, and olive oil. Add the beef to the marinade and refrigerate for at least 15 minutes. Preheat grill to medium-high heat. Remove the beef from the marinade and cook for 8-10 minutes per side, or until cooked to desired doneness. Meanwhile, toast bread until lightly browned. Serve the beef hot with the toasted bread and a sprinkle of cilantro if desired."
